OL,4,Crecognising Palestine would break
OL,5,Cinternational law
OL,7,FAs first reported by The Times
OL,8,Fnewspaper, the peers warned Sir Keir
OL,9,FStarmer's pledge to recognise
OL,10,FPalestine may breach international law
OL,11,Fas the territory may not meet the
OL,12,Fcriteria for statehood under the
OL,13,FMontevideo Convention, a treaty signed
OL,14,Fin 1933.
OL,16,F"I obviously respect what those
OL,17,Flawyers and colleagues in the Lords
OL,18,Fhave written, but I don't agree,"
OL,19,FThomas told ITV News.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
