OL,5,Cinternational law
OL,7,FIn their letter to Lord Hermer, the
OL,8,Fpeers said Palestine "does not meet
OL,9,Fthe international law criteria for
OL,10,Frecognition of a state, namely,
OL,11,Fdefined territory, a permanent
OL,12,Fpopulation, an effective government
OL,13,Fand the capacity to enter into
OL,14,Frelations with other states".
OL,16,FThere is no certainty over the borders
OL,17,Fof Palestine, they said, and no single
OL,18,Fgovernment, as Hamas and Fatah are
OL,19,Fenemies.
